args: Tee hee...\nEeeee hee hee hee hee...
This apple pie is insanely good!
I've had Luccy's smile replaying on\nendless loop in my head ever since! \nIt's enough to make a girl drool!
No, this is more than just good, Chelsea...
This is more than an apple pie.\nIt's an edible declaration of your love.
And I'm accepting each and every bite.\nChelsea, bake me one of these every day\nfor the rest of our lives together!
Thus did a parade of sweets grace the\ncouple's table every day, their love\nfuller than their bellies at dinnertime...
Then came the children. First one, then\ntwo, three... Before they knew it, the pitter-\npatter of twenty tiny feet filled their home!
A home warmed by a glowing hearth.\nA huge yard for teaching the kids archery.\nAnd a gigantic, fluffy, white dog as a pet!
EEEEEEE HEE HEE HEE HEE HEE!
So nice to have a clear vision of my future.\nNow, for tomorrow's Valentine's present—
Gold is the classic choice for wedding and\nengagement jewelry, though many\nyounger people choose silver as well.
Yes, yes, I see... Very interesting.
They're all so lovely! It just isn't a wedding\nwithout a shiny pair of matching earrings.\nI need to pick out the very best for us!
Oh, yes! Matching earrings are a powerful\nsymbol of your eternal union—proof of\na sylvan spouse's bond! Do take your time.
Ah, but is your partner not with you\ntoday to help you choose?
Nope! My Luccy's just too popular. He's\nalways in high demand. That's why I try\nto take care of these things for him.
Awww! He's so lucky to have you.\nI'm sure you'll enjoy a wonderful\npartnership together.
You think?! Heh. Hee hee hee...\nYou flatter me. I'll try my absolute best!
Now, have you made your decision?
I've gotta say, nothing draws my eye quite\nlike the bling here. It'll shine a guiding\nlight on the path of matrimony before us!
And then... I'd also like your best piece\nthat's infused with the power of love!
Infused with the...what of what, miss?
Y'know, like if Luccy gets hurt in battle and\nI pray to the heavens and his earring picks\nup my prayer and starts glowing and the
power of my love is like ZWING! and heals\nhis wounds miraculously and he's all like\nWOW! or if the two of us get split up, but
only in the geographic sense because we'll\nnever get split up relationship-wise but the\nrings would light up with the power of love
and guide us back to each other's arms so\nbasically a pair of earrings that will get us\nthrough any and all obstacles forever!
I'm afraid we don't have anything quite\nso, erm...magical in stock.

It's not magic; it's the whole key to our
happy future that I absolutely cannot live
without and will fully throw a fit if I can't
get, thanks!
Uhhh... Um... I could introduce you to a\nskilled goldsmith who can apply \nprotective properties?
The northern woods are home to a\nlegendary artisan with a deep knowledge\nof magic. He might be able to make—
Say no more. I'm on the case!
Honestly, though, I wouldn't recommend it.\nHis skill is rivaled only by his legendary\ntemper. He refuses our commissions and—
So that's what I want. Make it, please!
*sigh* Hold your horses, girl. I don't\njust go hammering out accessories for\nany lovesick fool who drops by.
Yes, my enchanted artifacts are quite\npowerful. But that's precisely why I can't\ncasually dole them out to strangers.
Don't worry! There's nothing casual about\nthe love between me and Luccy!
That... That isn't my point. Now, listen—
Then what IS your point? Our love stands\non the bedrock of two iron wills! Frankly,\nit's offensive you'd suggest otherwise.
Yes, and I'm saying that's not the... Look.\nReal love is about carving open your own\npath together. You can't just buy a magic—
That's exactly what I'm doing: carving a\npath! By any means necessary. Hee hee.
I'm sure you'll understand if you just\nhear me out. Now, listen while I extol\nthe strength of our love!
First, there's all of Luccy's best traits. He's\nbright and cheery and super popular and\nnice to everyone and he's a dreamer and—
—which is why I knew then and there!\nForever being his steadfast companion is\nmy calling. My role. My destiny!
Girl, I... Fine. You know what? Fine.
Huh? But I have four or five more\nhours of prepared material (plus\nvisual aids!) ready to go! Here, I'll—
MERCY! Please, no! I'll make them!\nAnything you want! Just please, spare me!
Here... They're done. Take 'em and go.
Wooow, they're SOOO pretty! A pair of\nmagic earrings to protect our fated love...
More like ＂lightly enchanted.＂\nAt the end of the day, no trinket will\nkeep your love alive. That's your job.
Awww, Mr. Craftsman Guy...!\nI promise you we'll live happily ever after!
I finally got my hands on the symbols of\nour love. Sit tight, Luccy. I'm on my way!
Hey. You catch that dame? Just walked\nout of the stubborn old goat's workshop\nwith some kinda jewelry.
You serious? The stingy old coot's pieces\nall go for a fortune at market.
And there went one with a skinny,\ndefenseless little waif of a girl...\nKeh heh heh. It's time for a shakedown.
